00:00:04:090000.Speaker: Howard
00:00:04:090000.Dialogue: Very nice. What's Leonard going to do? Give up the pawn or give up the position?

00:00:41:050000.Speaker: Howard
00:00:41:050000.Dialogue: Too bad. You know the rules of Secret Agent Laser Obstacle Chess.

00:00:46:080000.Speaker: Howard
00:00:46:080000.Dialogue: Leonard died again, Sheldon. You're up.

00:00:48:110000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:00:48:110000.Dialogue: Despite my deep love of chess, lasers and aerosol disinfectant, I must forfeit.

00:00:58:000000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:00:58:000000.Dialogue: Penny has a don't knock on my door before 11:00 or I punch you in the throat rule.

00:01:07:040000.Speaker: Howard
00:01:07:040000.Dialogue: You know what'd be a great idea? We get some girls over here and play Laser Optical Strip Chess.

00:01:14:060000.Speaker: Leonard
00:01:14:060000.Dialogue: Believe me, any girl who would be willing to play that, you don't want to see naked.

00:02:00:110000.Speaker: Penny

00:02:02:170000.Scene: Outside Penny’s door. Sheldon stands looking at his watch with his hand poised to knock. At the right moment he starts knocking.
00:02:02:170000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:02:02:170000.Dialogue: The contents are irrelevant. A legal bailment has been created. Does that mean nothing to you?

00:02:08:060000.Scene: Outside Penny’s door. Sheldon stands looking at his watch with his hand poised to knock. At the right moment he starts knocking.
00:02:08:060000.Speaker: Penny

00:02:11:040000.Scene: Outside Penny’s door. Sheldon stands looking at his watch with his hand poised to knock. At the right moment he starts knocking.
00:02:11:040000.Speaker: Penny
00:02:11:040000.Dialogue: - Let me show you what I'm doing.

00:02:23:070000.Scene: Outside Penny’s door. Sheldon stands looking at his watch with his hand poised to knock. At the right moment he starts knocking.
00:02:23:070000.Speaker: Penny
00:02:23:070000.Dialogue: Look, look! I started a business.

00:02:26:140000.Scene: Outside Penny’s door. Sheldon stands looking at his watch with his hand poised to knock. At the right moment he starts knocking.
00:02:26:140000.Speaker: Sheldon

00:02:30:190000.Scene: Outside Penny’s door. Sheldon stands looking at his watch with his hand poised to knock. At the right moment he starts knocking.
00:02:30:190000.Speaker: Penny
00:02:30:190000.Dialogue: No, I'm making flower barrettes. See? I call them Penny Blossoms. I made one for myself, then all the girls at work wanted one. I showed some to this lady who runs a shop in Old Town. She sells cards and homemade jewelry. She said she wanted to sell them. I said, Okay. And in one week, I made a $156.

00:02:45:200000.Scene: Outside Penny’s door. Sheldon stands looking at his watch with his hand poised to knock. At the right moment he starts knocking.
00:02:45:200000.Speaker: Sheldon

00:02:50:170000.Scene: Outside Penny’s door. Sheldon stands looking at his watch with his hand poised to knock. At the right moment he starts knocking.
00:02:50:170000.Speaker: Penny
00:02:50:170000.Dialogue: Don't you get it? If this takes off, I won't have to be a waitress anymore.

00:02:55:040000.Scene: Outside Penny’s door. Sheldon stands looking at his watch with his hand poised to knock. At the right moment he starts knocking.
00:02:55:040000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:02:55:040000.Dialogue: But then who will bring me my cheeseburger on Tuesday nights?

00:02:58:140000.Scene: Outside Penny’s door. Sheldon stands looking at his watch with his hand poised to knock. At the right moment he starts knocking.
00:02:58:140000.Speaker: Penny

00:03:01:170000.Scene: Outside Penny’s door. Sheldon stands looking at his watch with his hand poised to knock. At the right moment he starts knocking.
00:03:01:170000.Speaker: Penny

00:03:02:180000.Scene: Outside Penny’s door. Sheldon stands looking at his watch with his hand poised to knock. At the right moment he starts knocking.
00:03:02:180000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:03:02:180000.Dialogue: And you're going to let her handle my food?

00:03:04:220000.Scene: Outside Penny’s door. Sheldon stands looking at his watch with his hand poised to knock. At the right moment he starts knocking.
00:03:04:220000.Speaker: Penny

00:03:08:030000.Scene: Outside Penny’s door. Sheldon stands looking at his watch with his hand poised to knock. At the right moment he starts knocking.
00:03:08:030000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:03:08:030000.Dialogue: I think you're just making that up.

00:03:10:030000.Scene: Outside Penny’s door. Sheldon stands looking at his watch with his hand poised to knock. At the right moment he starts knocking.
00:03:10:030000.Speaker: Penny
00:03:10:030000.Dialogue: I'm sorry about your hamburger. I just don't want to be a waitress for the rest of my life.

00:03:14:110000.Scene: Outside Penny’s door. Sheldon stands looking at his watch with his hand poised to knock. At the right moment he starts knocking.
00:03:14:110000.Speaker: Leonard

00:03:16:140000.Scene: Outside Penny’s door. Sheldon stands looking at his watch with his hand poised to knock. At the right moment he starts knocking.
00:03:16:140000.Speaker: Penny

00:03:20:230000.Scene: Outside Penny’s door. Sheldon stands looking at his watch with his hand poised to knock. At the right moment he starts knocking.
00:03:20:230000.Speaker: Penny
00:03:20:230000.Dialogue: So, what do you think? I mean, this could be a business, right?

00:03:25:100000.Scene: Outside Penny’s door. Sheldon stands looking at his watch with his hand poised to knock. At the right moment he starts knocking.
00:03:25:100000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:03:25:100000.Dialogue: How many of these can you make a day?

00:03:27:130000.Scene: Outside Penny’s door. Sheldon stands looking at his watch with his hand poised to knock. At the right moment he starts knocking.
00:03:27:130000.Speaker: Penny

00:03:28:220000.Scene: Outside Penny’s door. Sheldon stands looking at his watch with his hand poised to knock. At the right moment he starts knocking.
00:03:28:220000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:03:28:220000.Dialogue: And how much profit do you make per... Penny Blossom?

00:03:32:220000.Scene: Outside Penny’s door. Sheldon stands looking at his watch with his hand poised to knock. At the right moment he starts knocking.
00:03:32:220000.Speaker: Penny

00:03:34:190000.Scene: Outside Penny’s door. Sheldon stands looking at his watch with his hand poised to knock. At the right moment he starts knocking.
00:03:34:190000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:03:34:190000.Dialogue: Of course you're not. All right...

00:03:38:070000.Scene: Outside Penny’s door. Sheldon stands looking at his watch with his hand poised to knock. At the right moment he starts knocking.
00:03:38:070000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:03:38:070000.Dialogue: Ten dollars a day times five days a week times 52 weeks a year is $2,600.

00:03:44:070000.Scene: Outside Penny’s door. Sheldon stands looking at his watch with his hand poised to knock. At the right moment he starts knocking.
00:03:44:070000.Speaker: Penny

00:03:46:230000.Scene: Outside Penny’s door. Sheldon stands looking at his watch with his hand poised to knock. At the right moment he starts knocking.
00:03:46:230000.Speaker: Penny
00:03:46:230000.Dialogue: I don't have to pay taxes on this stuff.

00:03:49:110000.Scene: Outside Penny’s door. Sheldon stands looking at his watch with his hand poised to knock. At the right moment he starts knocking.
00:03:49:110000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:03:49:110000.Dialogue: I believe the Internal Revenue Service would strongly disagree.

00:03:53:160000.Scene: Outside Penny’s door. Sheldon stands looking at his watch with his hand poised to knock. At the right moment he starts knocking.
00:03:53:160000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:03:53:160000.Dialogue: But, if you took advantage of modern marketing techniques, and you optimized your manufacturing process, you might be able to make this a viable business.

00:04:01:150000.Scene: Outside Penny’s door. Sheldon stands looking at his watch with his hand poised to knock. At the right moment he starts knocking.
00:04:01:150000.Speaker: Penny
00:04:01:150000.Dialogue: And you know about that stuff?

00:04:08:100000.Scene: Outside Penny’s door. Sheldon stands looking at his watch with his hand poised to knock. At the right moment he starts knocking.
00:04:08:100000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:04:08:100000.Dialogue: I'm a physicist. I have a working knowledge of the entire universe and everything it contains.

00:04:17:130000.Scene: Outside Penny’s door. Sheldon stands looking at his watch with his hand poised to knock. At the right moment he starts knocking.
00:04:17:130000.Speaker: Penny

00:04:31:120000.Scene: Outside Penny’s door. Sheldon stands looking at his watch with his hand poised to knock. At the right moment he starts knocking.
00:04:31:120000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:04:31:120000.Dialogue: I have a working knowledge of the important things in the universe. - Good luck.

00:04:35:170000.Scene: Outside Penny’s door. Sheldon stands looking at his watch with his hand poised to knock. At the right moment he starts knocking.
00:04:35:170000.Speaker: Penny
00:04:35:170000.Dialogue: - Sheldon, hold on. Could you maybe show me how to make more money with this?

00:04:42:230000.Scene: Outside Penny’s door. Sheldon stands looking at his watch with his hand poised to knock. At the right moment he starts knocking.
00:04:42:230000.Speaker: Sheldon

00:04:45:100000.Scene: Outside Penny’s door. Sheldon stands looking at his watch with his hand poised to knock. At the right moment he starts knocking.
00:04:45:100000.Speaker: Penny

00:04:47:050000.Scene: Outside Penny’s door. Sheldon stands looking at his watch with his hand poised to knock. At the right moment he starts knocking.
00:04:47:050000.Speaker: Penny

00:04:52:140000.Scene: Outside Penny’s door. Sheldon stands looking at his watch with his hand poised to knock. At the right moment he starts knocking.
00:04:52:140000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:04:52:140000.Dialogue: Just to be clear here, you're asking for my assistance. And you understand that will involve me telling you what to do?

00:05:03:020000.Scene: Outside Penny’s door. Sheldon stands looking at his watch with his hand poised to knock. At the right moment he starts knocking.
00:05:03:020000.Speaker: Penny

00:05:04:230000.Scene: Outside Penny’s door. Sheldon stands looking at his watch with his hand poised to knock. At the right moment he starts knocking.
00:05:04:230000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:05:04:230000.Dialogue: And you're not allowed to be sarcastic or snide to me while I'm doing so.

00:05:13:020000.Scene: Outside Penny’s door. Sheldon stands looking at his watch with his hand poised to knock. At the right moment he starts knocking.
00:05:13:020000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:05:13:020000.Dialogue: Good. Let's begin with the premise that everything you've done up to this point is wrong.

00:05:21:040000.Scene: Outside Penny’s door. Sheldon stands looking at his watch with his hand poised to knock. At the right moment he starts knocking.
00:05:21:040000.Speaker: Sheldon

00:05:23:210000.Scene: Outside Penny’s door. Sheldon stands looking at his watch with his hand poised to knock. At the right moment he starts knocking.
00:05:23:210000.Speaker: Penny
00:05:23:210000.Dialogue: No, sorry. Wait! Please come back!

00:05:53:050000.Scene: Penny’s apartment. Penny is making a barette. Sheldon is timing her.
00:05:53:050000.Speaker: Penny

00:05:57:180000.Scene: Penny’s apartment. Penny is making a barette. Sheldon is timing her.
00:05:57:180000.Speaker: Penny

00:06:09:100000.Scene: Penny’s apartment. Penny is making a barette. Sheldon is timing her.
00:06:09:100000.Speaker: Penny

00:06:10:140000.Scene: Penny’s apartment. Penny is making a barette. Sheldon is timing her.
00:06:10:140000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:06:10:140000.Dialogue: There are children in a sneaker factory in Indonesia who outearn you.

00:06:15:220000.Scene: Penny’s apartment. Penny is making a barette. Sheldon is timing her.
00:06:15:220000.Speaker: Penny

00:06:17:130000.Scene: Penny’s apartment. Penny is making a barette. Sheldon is timing her.
00:06:17:130000.Speaker: Sheldon

00:06:20:150000.Scene: Penny’s apartment. Penny is making a barette. Sheldon is timing her.
00:06:20:150000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:06:20:150000.Dialogue: - Want me to show my work?

00:06:23:020000.Scene: Penny’s apartment. Penny is making a barette. Sheldon is timing her.
00:06:23:020000.Speaker: Penny
00:06:23:020000.Dialogue: Please tell me what to do about it.

00:06:25:000000.Scene: Penny’s apartment. Penny is making a barette. Sheldon is timing her.
00:06:25:000000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:06:25:000000.Dialogue: All right. Are you familiar with the development that resulted from Honoré Blanc's 1778 use of interchangeable parts?

00:06:36:120000.Scene: Penny’s apartment. Penny is making a barette. Sheldon is timing her.
00:06:36:120000.Speaker: Sheldon

00:06:38:210000.Scene: Penny’s apartment. Penny is making a barette. Sheldon is timing her.
00:06:38:210000.Speaker: Penny
00:06:38:210000.Dialogue: If I'm not allowed to be snide, you're not allowed to be condescending.

00:06:42:230000.Scene: Penny’s apartment. Penny is making a barette. Sheldon is timing her.
00:06:42:230000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:06:42:230000.Dialogue: That wasn't a part of our original agreement, and I don't agree to it now.

00:06:47:030000.Scene: Penny’s apartment. Penny is making a barette. Sheldon is timing her.
00:06:47:030000.Speaker: Penny
00:06:47:030000.Dialogue: Fine. How are we supposed to set up machines and conveyor belts in my apartment?

00:06:51:090000.Scene: Penny’s apartment. Penny is making a barette. Sheldon is timing her.
00:06:51:090000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:06:51:090000.Dialogue: You're thinking of the moving assembly line, an understandable but not excusable mistake.

00:06:58:000000.Scene: Penny’s apartment. Penny is making a barette. Sheldon is timing her.
00:06:58:000000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:06:58:000000.Dialogue: The moving assembly line, that was introduced by Henry Ford in 1908. That innovation is what made possible our modern consumer culture by enabling a low-unit cost for manufactured goods. I guess that isn't one of the topics discussed on your Radiohead.

00:07:15:090000.Speaker: Leonard
00:07:15:090000.Dialogue: Let's go. We're going to miss the coming attractions.

00:07:23:220000.Speaker: Howard
00:07:23:220000.Dialogue: I think I bruised a testicle capturing that last pawn.

00:07:31:050000.Speaker: Howard
00:07:31:050000.Dialogue: Please pay attention and listen to me Give me some time to blow the man down I'm a deepwater sailor just come from Hong Kong To me way, hey, blow the man down If you give me some whiskey I'll sing you a song Give me some time to blow the man down.

00:08:08:020000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:08:08:020000.Dialogue: I assume you're referring to the sea shanty. It's a rhythmic work song designed to increase productivity.

00:08:13:050000.Speaker: Penny
00:08:13:050000.Dialogue: It's crazy, but it totally works. We made this Penny Blossom in under three minutes.

00:08:18:020000.Speaker: Leonard
00:08:18:020000.Dialogue: Terrific, but that kind of raises more questions than it answers.

00:08:23:010000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:08:23:010000.Dialogue: Penny's making hair accessories. I'm helping her optimize her manufacturing process. Break's over.

00:08:31:020000.Speaker: Howard
00:08:31:020000.Dialogue: Hold on. What are you using as a bonding agent?

00:08:39:160000.Speaker: Leonard
00:08:39:160000.Dialogue: What if we infused the bottom layer with silicone-RTV to provide a better mounting surface?

00:08:46:230000.Speaker: Howard
00:08:46:230000.Dialogue: What are your marketing and distribution channels?

00:08:49:070000.Speaker: Penny
00:08:49:070000.Dialogue: There are the waitresses at my work, and this cute, little shop in Old Town.

00:08:55:120000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:08:55:120000.Dialogue: I'm thinking that we set her up with a hosted e-commerce system to start.

00:08:59:100000.Speaker: Howard
00:08:59:100000.Dialogue: Why not eliminate the middle man? We could install a small server farm with a static IP in her bedroom.

00:09:06:020000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:09:06:020000.Dialogue: Of course, but before we set up marketing and distribution, we should finish optimizing the manufacturing process. To start with, she has a terrible problem with moisture-induced glitter clump.

00:09:30:160000.Speaker: Howard
00:09:30:160000.Dialogue: They dance, they sweat, they clump.

00:09:37:140000.Speaker: Leonard
00:09:37:140000.Dialogue: Are you thinking about adding a desiccant like calcium sulfate?

00:09:40:160000.Speaker: Howard
00:09:40:160000.Dialogue: Actually, I'm thinking about this one stripper named Vega.

00:09:47:040000.Speaker: Howard
00:09:47:040000.Dialogue: But sure, calcium sulfate could work.

00:09:50:120000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:09:50:120000.Dialogue: Let's think out of the box for a moment. How about a molecular sieve?

00:09:57:070000.Speaker: Penny
00:09:57:070000.Dialogue: I've got a spaghetti strainer in the kitchen.

00:10:08:040000.Speaker: Leonard
00:10:08:040000.Dialogue: We could liberate some micro-porous charcoal from the chem lab.

00:10:11:090000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:10:11:090000.Dialogue: Great. Raj, why don't you and Howard, go get the charcoal? Leonard, why don't you start working on some preliminary Web site designs. I'll make some space in our apartment so we can move the manufacturing process.

00:10:25:200000.Speaker: Penny
00:10:25:200000.Dialogue: Wait, what am I going to do?

00:10:27:220000.Speaker: Leonard
00:10:27:220000.Dialogue: It's your business. Do whatever you want.

00:10:32:140000.Speaker: Penny
00:10:32:140000.Dialogue: Okay, cool. I'm going to take a nap.

00:10:41:210000.Speaker: Leonard
00:10:41:210000.Dialogue: I'm still tweaking things a little bit, but this will give you the general idea of the Web site.

00:10:51:060000.Speaker: Leonard
00:10:51:060000.Dialogue: So, what do you guys think?

00:10:55:010000.Speaker: Howard
00:10:55:010000.Dialogue: Pretty much any way I say that is going to hurt his feelings.

00:11:04:140000.Speaker: Leonard
00:11:04:140000.Dialogue: Not you. I wasn't asking you.

00:11:09:100000.Speaker: Penny
00:11:09:100000.Dialogue: Well, it's a little juvenile. It kind of looks like the MySpace page of a 13-year-old girl.

00:11:17:170000.Speaker: Howard
00:11:17:170000.Dialogue: Please. Dateline could use it to attract predators.

00:11:24:220000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:11:24:220000.Dialogue: This is your enterprise, so it's ultimately your decision, but based on the quality of his work, I'd strongly recommend that we let Leonard go.

00:11:35:110000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:11:35:110000.Dialogue: What I want is irrelevant. This is Penny's decision.

00:11:41:020000.Speaker: Leonard
00:11:41:020000.Dialogue: Excuse me, but if I did such a bad job then why do we already have orders?

00:11:45:190000.Speaker: Leonard
00:11:45:190000.Dialogue: Look. Mrs. Fiona Fondell from Huntsville, Alabama has ordered two.

00:11:56:020000.Speaker: Penny
00:11:56:020000.Dialogue: Thank you, Penny Blossoms. These will be perfect to cover my bald spot.

00:12:04:120000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:12:04:120000.Dialogue: Camouflaging bald spots. That's primarily a male concern. Perhaps we could expand our market.

00:12:11:030000.Speaker: Penny
00:12:11:030000.Dialogue: How are flower barrettes going to appeal to men?

00:12:23:090000.Speaker: Penny
00:12:23:090000.Dialogue: Wait a minute, you want to make a hair barrette with Bluetooth?

00:12:33:190000.Speaker: Leonard
00:12:33:190000.Dialogue: Holy crap. Someone just ordered a thousand Penny Blossoms.

00:12:37:220000.Speaker: Penny
00:12:37:220000.Dialogue: Get out! Who needs a thousand sparkly flower barrettes with rhinestones?

00:12:43:150000.Speaker: Leonard
00:12:43:150000.Dialogue: The Fifth Annual East Rutherford, New Jersey, Gay, Lesbian, Bisexual and Transgender Alliance Luau.

00:12:50:160000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:12:50:160000.Dialogue: Another market to expand into... balding gay men.

00:12:54:230000.Speaker: Howard
00:12:54:230000.Dialogue: And I'll bet lesbians love Bluetooth.

00:13:00:030000.Speaker: Penny
00:13:00:030000.Dialogue: Wait, why does it say one-day rush? Since when do we offer a one-day rush?

00:13:06:170000.Speaker: Penny
00:13:06:170000.Dialogue: Yeah, but they don't have to glue the books together.

00:13:10:120000.Speaker: Penny
00:13:10:120000.Dialogue: How the hell are we going to make a thousand Penny Blossoms in one day?

00:13:13:150000.Speaker: Leonard
00:13:13:150000.Dialogue: Don't yell at me. I'm not manufacturing. I'm just Web design.

00:13:17:130000.Speaker: Penny
00:13:17:130000.Dialogue: I'm gonna have to call them and cancel the order.

00:13:19:170000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:13:19:170000.Dialogue: Excuse me, but was this not your goal? Financial independence through entrepreneurial brilliance and innovation? My brilliance and innovation, of course, but still.

00:13:31:060000.Speaker: Penny
00:13:31:060000.Dialogue: I just don't see how we can pull this off.

00:13:33:150000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:13:33:150000.Dialogue: That, right there, that equivocation and self-doubt, that is not the American spirit.

00:13:40:020000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:13:40:020000.Dialogue: Did Davy Crockett quit at the Alamo? Did Jim Bowie?

00:13:43:210000.Speaker: Howard
00:13:43:210000.Dialogue: They didn't quit. They were massacred... by like a gazillion angry Mexicans.

00:13:53:150000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:13:53:150000.Dialogue: Let me put it this way. Your gross receipts on this one order will be over $3,000 for one night's work.

00:14:20:090000.Scene: The same, later. Sheldon and Penny are making barettes, singing “She’ll be coming round the mountain.”
00:14:20:090000.Speaker: Raj
00:14:20:090000.Dialogue: You know, if I wanted to spend my Saturday nights doing this, I could have stayed in India.

00:14:27:180000.Scene: The same, later. Sheldon and Penny are making barettes, singing “She’ll be coming round the mountain.”
00:14:27:180000.Speaker: Howard
00:14:27:180000.Dialogue: Stop with the fake third world crap. Your father's a gynecologist. And you had a house full of servants.

00:14:33:050000.Scene: The same, later. Sheldon and Penny are making barettes, singing “She’ll be coming round the mountain.”
00:14:33:050000.Speaker: Raj
00:14:33:050000.Dialogue: We only had four servants. And two of them were children.

00:14:39:150000.Scene: The same, later. Sheldon and Penny are making barettes, singing “She’ll be coming round the mountain.”
00:14:39:150000.Speaker: Leonard

00:14:40:200000.Scene: The same, later. Sheldon and Penny are making barettes, singing “She’ll be coming round the mountain.”
00:14:40:200000.Speaker: Raj
00:14:40:200000.Dialogue: We have 128 assorted Penny Blossoms ready to ship.

00:16:27:180000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:16:27:180000.Dialogue: Look at Planck's Constant. People say it's arbitrary. It could not be less arbitrary. If it varied slightly, life as we know it would not exist. Bam!

00:16:57:030000.Speaker: Sheldon
